Let me start by saying we generally love Chipotle; this is not our favorite location.  In general, the service and food has been spotty here.  They are generally slow. Most of the time they seem to skimp on what goes in the bowls (our usual order).  Sometimes the proteins are barely seasoned; sometimes they are way too salty, and often it is tough.  Usually, it is barely warm. We have held off on giving a review until last night.  I placed an order online, and it said it would be ready by 6:15pm.  Knowing this location, I knew that was optimistic but thought surely it would be ready by 6:30.  That said, I still arrived at 6:15pm.  I stood in the online pickup line and no one of the staff even acknowledged my presence until about 6:40pm - even though people who arrived after me got food before me.  Finally at 6:52, I asked if they could please give me an update as my food was supposed to have been ready by 6:15pm.  You would have thought I asked the guy to move a mountain.  I finally walked out with my food at 7:00pm.  Living nearby, we were eating by 7:05, but the food was already cold. We likely won't be back here.

My family and I were in the area for church, when the kids asked for Chipotle. We walked in at 11 A.M, 15 minutes after they opened and my kids pointed out that we were the only ones in there...they've never seen an empty Chipotle lol! There were 3 team members who turned around at the sound of us coming in, then proceeded to turn back around and continue what they were doing, without so much as a "hello, we will be with you in a moment." No "hi" or anything. We walk up to the counter and continued to be ignored. We waited a couple minutes, then I asked my husband if he wanted to leave, as nobody was assisting us. Once I asked that, one team member turned around and asked us something...I couldn't hear him, as he was speaking very low and quietly. He had a look of disgust on his face, as if he didn't even want to be at work that day. I assumed he asked what I wanted, so I proceeded to order a chicken bowl. I didn't get a good look at the chicken until it was actually in my bowl... it wasn't until then that I saw every single piece of chicken was burnt! However, I'm not that picky, so I went with it! My husband ordered steak tacos and the kids got quesadillas. I asked for 2 chicken and 2 regular cheese...he only put chicken on 1 of them. I had to tell him, again, to put chicken on the other quesadilla. Anyway, I grabbed the kids' empty soda cups to fill them up. As soon as I pushed the lever, soda sprayed all over me! That's when I realized the spouts hadn't been attached that morning! I had to tell the cashier, who then quickly attached them for me. He was the friendliest one in the bunch! I got the soda, sat back down, and started eating my food. Now, I don't mind a bit of burnt food, however, that much burnt chicken was very disappointing. I told my husband I didn't really like the taste of it, and he replies, "yeah, um, and my steak is cold, too." I thought maybe the veggies and cheese had cooled his steak off a bit..... no, not the case! I tried a piece and it was, indeed, cold! I told him, considering the service and quality of food we'd received thus far, to bring his tacos back up and get them remade. He went up, without his food, and asked if their meat is prepared fresh? They said yes, to which my husband responded that their steak was cold, as if it came out of a refrigerator. A lady at the counter told my husband there was no way it could be cold because they had JUST prepared it. That part annoyed me a bit, because we are not the type to make up reasons we don't like food. I COULD'VE said something about my burnt burrito bowl, but I did not. Anyhow, my husband sat back down and continued eating his cold tacos.  He was thirsty and realized he didn't get himself a drink, so he went back up to the counter and asked for a complimentary soda to make up for the tacos... they obliged. Once we finished, we cleaned up and left, and of course, there were no parting salutations from the team. Call me spoiled, if you will, but our regular Chipotle, at Arundel Mills Mall, is ALWAYS on point! They greet you as soon as you walk in the door, they are very thorough in their work, and they will say goodbye as you leave, no matter how slow or busy the restaurant is! THAT is true customer service! I gave 2 stars... one for the friendly cashier and one for the complimentary soda. Other than that, it was a disappointing experience!
